#include <iostream>
#include <stack>   // Stack library in C++
using namespace std;

// Function to check if the brackets are balanced
bool isBalanced(string exp) {
    stack<char> s;  // Create a stack to store brackets

    // Traverse the expression character by character
    for (char ch : exp) {
        // 1Ô∏è‚É£ If opening bracket, push into stack
        if (ch == '(' || ch == '{' || ch == '[') {
            s.push(ch);
        }

        // 2Ô∏è‚É£ If closing bracket, check stack top
        else if (ch == ')' || ch == '}' || ch == ']') {
            // If stack empty, means no opening bracket available
            if (s.empty()) {
                return false;
            }

            char top = s.top();  // Look at top bracket
            s.pop();             // Remove it for checking

            // Check if top matches with the closing bracket
            if ((ch == ')' && top != '(') ||
                (ch == '}' && top != '{') ||
                (ch == ']' && top != '[')) {
                return false;  // Mismatch found
            }
        }
    }

    // 3Ô∏è‚É£ At the end, stack must be empty (all matched)
    return s.empty();
}

int main() {
    string expression;
    cout << "Enter an expression: ";
    cin >> expression;

    if (isBalanced(expression))
        cout << "Expression is well parenthesized (balanced)." << endl;
    else
        cout << "Expression is NOT balanced!" << endl;

    return 0;
}






üß© Algorithm for C-6: Check Balanced Parentheses
Aim:

To check whether a given expression has balanced delimiters such as
( ), { }, and [ ] using a stack data structure.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Start
2Ô∏è‚É£ Initialize Stack:

Create an empty stack S to store opening brackets.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Input Expression:

Read the expression exp (string of characters).

4Ô∏è‚É£ Scan Expression from Left to Right:

For each character ch in exp:

Step 4.1:

If ch is an opening bracket ('(', '{', '['):
‚Üí Push ch onto the stack.

Step 4.2:

If ch is a closing bracket (')', '}', ']'):

If stack is empty, expression is not balanced ‚Üí Stop.

Else:

Pop the top element from stack (say top).

Check if top and ch are of the same type:

( and ), { and }, [ and ]

If not matching ‚Üí expression not balanced ‚Üí Stop.

5Ô∏è‚É£ After Scanning Entire Expression:

If stack is empty, then expression is well parenthesized (balanced).

If stack not empty, then expression is not balanced (some brackets left unmatched).

6Ô∏è‚É£ Stop
